Afrikaner rights group AfriForum plans to lay criminal charges against 100 social media users for Incitement to commit murder among other charges.The group is scheduled to lay the charges tomorrow at the Lyttelton Police station, Centurion.AfriForum will submit 100 affidavits to the SAPS tomorrow. The affidavits pertain to incidents of alleged racism, hate speech and incitement to violence made by the different social media users and will be accompanied by screenshots of their statements.See the full list of social media users below&#8211;Kutullo Madisha&nbsp;&nbsp;